description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse (General, Learning Disabilities or Mental Health)&lt;/strong&gt; with a passion for delivering the best quality of care to join us at our nursing home located in Knutsford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be working 36 or 24 hours per week (7.45pm – 7.45am; 1-4 nights per week) at Cygnet Tabley House&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tabley House&lt;/strong&gt; is a nursing home close to Knutsford in Cheshire which offers 24-hour nursing care in a unique and charming environment.The home supports people with a range of different needs including those living with dementia and individuals looking for short or longer stays, complex health care needs, convalescent care or post-operative support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply now to enjoy excellent career prospects while reaping the rewards of making a difference to others – every day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Day-to-Day…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be responsible for the co-ordination, assessment, planning, implementation and evaluation of individual resident programs of care with a focus on person centred care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaising with GP&#39;s and other professionals where necessary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support empowerment of residents having regard for their dignity rights whilst maintaining professional responsibility for individuals in our care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure that individual care plans are completed and maintained in conjunction with Resident, Relatives and other Health Care Professionals, and in accordance with NMC guidelines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer prescribed medicines with Healthcare procedure and Healthcare Commission guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Cygnet? We’ll offer you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS and employee discount scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;50% NMC registration renewal paid by Cygnet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free meals on duty&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free parking&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RCNi membership &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bespoke career pathways&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company paid Life Assurance scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Smart Health Toolkit- Providing you with Fitness Programmes, Nutrition consultation and Health checks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Y&lt;strong&gt;ou are…&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are newly Qualified or an Experienced Registered Nurse with a current Pin Number&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have an understanding of latest nursing practices and are able to deputise in a clinical lead role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have the capacity to maintain documentation and undertake audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compassionate and focused on patient care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in working with older adults&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cygnet Health Care&lt;/strong&gt; has been providing a national network of high quality specialist mental health services for 30 years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Registered Nurse&lt;/strong&gt; joining our nursing cohort at Cygnet Health Care, you will become part of a team that is focused on delivering exceptional care in a high quality environment. You will be working alongside other dedicated nurses who are keen to develop themselves as you are.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tabley House &lt;strong&gt;CQC &lt;/strong&gt;overall rating - &lt;strong&gt;Good&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ready to make a positive change? Please click on the ‘apply now’ link below.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
